A4.text: The Delaware River has two branches that rise in the Catskill Mountains of New York

A5.text: The East Branch of the Delaware River begins from a small pond south of Grand Gorge in the town of Roxbury in Delaware County

A6.text: Maps from the 18th and 19th centuries consistently mark the border of the Catskill Mountains as the East Branch of the Delaware River
